Preheat your oven to 100°C. Put a large #saucepan{} of @water with a pinch of @salt on to boil for the broccoli. Halve, peel and finely chop the @echalion shallot{1}(halved, peeled and finely chopped). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Slice each @chestnut mushrooms{150} into about four pieces. Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1/2}(finely chopped) (stalks and all).

Add the @broccoli florets{200} to the boiling water and simmer until just cooked, ~{3-4%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and keep to the side.

> Don't worry about it going cold, it will be warmed up in the sauce later!

Meanwhile, heat a glug of @oil in a #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @gnocchi{350} and fry until crispy around the edges, about ~{8%minutes}.

> Cook the gnocchi in batches if your frying pan is not big enough to cook it all in a single layer (you want it brown and crispy).

Once cooked, transfer the gnocchi to a #baking tray{} and place on the middle shelf of your #oven{} to keep warm until the end. Keep the pan!

Heat another splash of @oil in your now empty frying pan over high heat. Add the shallot and @pancetta{60}(smoked, lardons) and cook, stirring, until the pancetta has browned and the shallot is soft, ~{4%minutes}. Add the mushrooms and fry until they are soft and browned, ~{5%minutes}. Finally, add the garlic, stir together and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @water{100} and a few grinds of @black pepper{} to your frying pan. Allow to simmer over medium heat until the water has reduced, ~{8-10%minutes}. Once reduced, stir the @creme fraiche{100} into the sauce. Add in the gnocchi and broccoli and give it all a good stir, making sure everything is nicely warmed through.

Taste for seasoning and add more salt and black pepper if necessary. Divide the gnocchi between your #bowls{}, grate over the @hard Italian style cheese{40}(grated) and top with a sprinkling of parsley.